h3cFcZoneServer.name: h3cFcZoneServer

revisions.description: Initial version of this MIB module.

h3cFcZoneServer.contactinfo: Platform Team Hangzhou H3C Tech. Co., Ltd. Hai-Dian District Beijing P.R. China http://www.h3c.com Zip:100085
h3cFcZoneServer.description: This MIB module is intended for management of FC(Fibre Channel) Zoning entities, including Basic Zoning Management and Enhanced Zoning Management.

H3cFcZsGenName.name: H3cFcZsGenName
H3cFcZsGenName.description: Represents the general names for a Zone Set, Zone or Zone alias object. Each octet in this string is an ASCII code for an English letter, digit, or special character such as the dollar sign ($), minus sign (-), caret (^), or underscores (_). This string must contain at least one character and must start with an English letter.

H3cFcZsGenNameOrZero.name: H3cFcZsGenNameOrZero
H3cFcZsGenNameOrZero.description: Represents the general names for a Zone Set, Zone or Zone alias object. Each octet in this string is an ASCII code for an English letter, digit, or special character such as the dollar sign ($), minus sign (-), caret (^), or underscores (_). This string must start with an English letter.

H3cFcZsZoneMemberType.name: H3cFcZsZoneMemberType
H3cFcZsZoneMemberType.description: Represents the addressing mechanism by which a member is identified: 'fcid' - FC ID of N_Port. 'fwwn' - WWN(World Wide Name) of F_Port. 'pwwn' - WWN(World Wide Name) of N_Port. 'aliasName' - Zone alias name.

h3cFcZsServerTable.name: h3cFcZsServerTable
h3cFcZsServerTable.description: A table that contains information about the Zone Servers in each VSAN and provides the capability to perform operations on their Zone Server databases.

h3cFcZsServerEntry.name: h3cFcZsServerEntry
h3cFcZsServerEntry.description: Each entry contains information specific to a Zone Server for a particular VSAN.

h3cFcZsZoneModeCfg.name: h3cFcZsZoneModeCfg
h3cFcZsZoneModeCfg.description: The operational mode of the Zone Server. Setting this object to 'enhanced' is a request to set the operational mode of the Zone Server to Enhanced mode. This is possible only if all switches in the Fibre Channel Fabric are capable of working in Enhanced mode. Setting this object to 'basic' is a request to set the operational mode of the Zone Server to Basic mode.

h3cFcZsHardZoneEnable.name: h3cFcZsHardZoneEnable
h3cFcZsHardZoneEnable.description: This object indicates whether this switch, no matter in Basic or Enhanced mode, enforces Hard Zoning in this VSAN.

h3cFcZsDistributeRule.name: h3cFcZsDistributeRule
h3cFcZsDistributeRule.description: This object specifies whether a complete distribution (or merge) will be applied when an activation(or merge) happened in Basic mode. If this object is set to 'full', both the Active Zone Set and Zone Set Database will be distributed (or merged) when an activation operation(or merge) is performed. If this object is set to 'activeOnly', only the Active Zone Set will be distributed(or merged) when an activation operation(or merge) is performed. The value 'none' is meaningless and can be used only in Enhanced mode.

h3cFcZsDefaultZoneSetting.name: h3cFcZsDefaultZoneSetting
h3cFcZsDefaultZoneSetting.description: This object controls the Zoning flag that governs the behavior of the Default Zone in this VSAN. If this object is set to 'permit', the members of the Default Zone in this VSAN can communicate with each other. If this object is set to 'deny', the members of the Default Zone in this VSAN cannot communicate with each other.

h3cFcZsMergeControlSetting.name: h3cFcZsMergeControlSetting
h3cFcZsMergeControlSetting.description: This object controls the Enhanced Zoning flag that indicates the Merge Control Setting for this VSAN. It is meaningful only in Enhanced mode: 'none' - This value is meaningless and only can be used in Basic mode. 'allow' - A switch may join the Fabric only if its Zoning Database is able to merge with the Fabric's Zoning Database. 'restrict' - A switch may join the Fabric only if its Zoning Database is equal to the Fabric's Zoning Database.

h3cFcZsServerLastResult.name: h3cFcZsServerLastResult
h3cFcZsServerLastResult.description: Current operational status of the latest configuration in this VSAN: 'none' - No corresponding operation has been performed yet. 'success' - The configuration was performed successfully. 'busy' - The configuration was performed unsuccessfully, because the system is busy with another zoning operation. 'noSupportInFabric' - The configuration was performed unsuccessfully, because one or more switches in this Fabric don't support Enhanced zoning. 'noSupportInBasic' - The configuration was performed unsuccessfully, because it is not supported in Basic mode. 'noSupportInEnhanced' - The configuration was performed unsuccessfully, because it is not supported in Enhanced mode. 'activeZoneSetTooBig' - The configuration was performed unsuccessfully, because the Active Zone Set is too large to be supported. 'otherFault' - The configuration was performed unsuccessfully for other reasons.

h3cFcZsZonesetTable.name: h3cFcZsZonesetTable
h3cFcZsZonesetTable.description: A table that contains information about each Zone Set in the Zone Set Database of the Zone Servers in a specified VSAN.

h3cFcZsZonesetEntry.name: h3cFcZsZonesetEntry
h3cFcZsZonesetEntry.description: Each entry contains the information of a Zone Set configured in a specified VSAN.

h3cFcZsZonesetIndex.name: h3cFcZsZonesetIndex
h3cFcZsZonesetIndex.description: The index of a Zone Set, which uniquely identifies a Zone Set in the Zone Set Database on local switch.

h3cFcZsZonesetName.name: h3cFcZsZonesetName
h3cFcZsZonesetName.description: The name of this Zone Set, which should be unique within a VSAN. The Zone Set can be renamed by setting this object to a new value.

h3cFcZsZonesetRowStatus.name: h3cFcZsZonesetRowStatus
h3cFcZsZonesetRowStatus.description: The status of this conceptual row.

h3cFcZsZoneTable.name: h3cFcZsZoneTable
h3cFcZsZoneTable.description: This table contains information about all the Zones in the Zone Set Database of the Zone Servers in each VSAN.

h3cFcZsZoneEntry.name: h3cFcZsZoneEntry
h3cFcZsZoneEntry.description: Each entry contains information about a Zone in the Zone Set Database in a specified VSAN.

h3cFcZsZoneIndex.name: h3cFcZsZoneIndex
h3cFcZsZoneIndex.description: An index value that uniquely identifies this Zone in the Zone Set Database on local switch.

h3cFcZsZoneName.name: h3cFcZsZoneName
h3cFcZsZoneName.description: The name of this Zone, which should be unique within a VSAN. The Zone can be renamed by setting this object to a new value.

h3cFcZsZonePairwiseEnable.name: h3cFcZsZonePairwiseEnable
h3cFcZsZonePairwiseEnable.description: This object specifies whether Pairwise Zoning is enabled in this Zone. When Pairwise Zoning is enabled in a Zone, the behaviors of members in this Zone will be controlled through their roles. The members with the same role ('initiator' or 'target') can't communicate with each other, but those with different roles or with the same role 'both' can communicate with each other. When Pairwise Zoning is disabled in a Zone, the behaviors of members in this Zone will not be affected by their roles.

h3cFcZsZoneRowStatus.name: h3cFcZsZoneRowStatus
h3cFcZsZoneRowStatus.description: The status of this conceptual row.

h3cFcZsSetZoneTable.name: h3cFcZsSetZoneTable
h3cFcZsSetZoneTable.description: This table specifies which Zone belongs to which Zone Set in the Zone Set Database of the Zone Servers.

h3cFcZsSetZoneEntry.name: h3cFcZsSetZoneEntry
h3cFcZsSetZoneEntry.description: Each entry specifies that a particular Zone is one of the Zones that form a particular Zone Set in the Zone Set database of a specified VSAN. When a row in this table exists, it references one row in the h3cFcZsZonesetTable and one row in the h3cFcZsZoneTable. The agent must ensure that both such rows when referenced by an active row in this table, do exist and have a status of 'active'.

h3cFcZsSetZoneRowStatus.name: h3cFcZsSetZoneRowStatus
h3cFcZsSetZoneRowStatus.description: The status of this conceptual row.

h3cFcZsZoneAliasTable.name: h3cFcZsZoneAliasTable
h3cFcZsZoneAliasTable.description: This table contains information about the Zone aliases in the Zone Set Database of the Zone Server in each VSAN.

h3cFcZsZoneAliasEntry.name: h3cFcZsZoneAliasEntry
h3cFcZsZoneAliasEntry.description: Each entry contains information about a Zone alias in the Zone Set Database of a particular VSAN.

h3cFcZsZoneAliasIndex.name: h3cFcZsZoneAliasIndex
h3cFcZsZoneAliasIndex.description: An index value that uniquely identifies this Zone alias within the Zone Set Database.

h3cFcZsZoneAliasName.name: h3cFcZsZoneAliasName
h3cFcZsZoneAliasName.description: The name of this Zone alias, which should be unique within a VSAN. The Zone alias can be renamed by setting this object to a new value.

h3cFcZsZoneAliasRowStatus.name: h3cFcZsZoneAliasRowStatus
h3cFcZsZoneAliasRowStatus.description: The status of this conceptual row.

h3cFcZsZoneMemberTable.name: h3cFcZsZoneMemberTable
h3cFcZsZoneMemberTable.description: This table contains all members of a Zone/Zone alias and information about those members in the Zone Set Database of the Zone Server in each VSAN.

h3cFcZsZoneMemberEntry.name: h3cFcZsZoneMemberEntry
h3cFcZsZoneMemberEntry.description: Each entry represents the relationship between a member and (one of) its 'parent(s)', i.e., a Zone or Zone alias the member belongs, within a particular VSAN.

h3cFcZsZoneMemberParentType.name: h3cFcZsZoneMemberParentType
h3cFcZsZoneMemberParentType.description: This object determines whether this member belongs to a Zone or Zone alias.

h3cFcZsZoneMemberParentIndex.name: h3cFcZsZoneMemberParentIndex
h3cFcZsZoneMemberParentIndex.description: This object contains the index value of the Zone or Zone alias to which this member belongs. If the value of the corresponding instance of h3cFcZsZoneMemberParentType is 'zone', this object will contain the value of the h3cFcZsZoneIndex object of the Zone to which this member belongs. If the value of the corresponding instance of h3cFcZsZoneMemberParentType is 'alias', this object will contain the value of the h3cFcZsAliasIndex object of the Zone alias to which this member belongs.

h3cFcZsZoneMemberIndex.name: h3cFcZsZoneMemberIndex
h3cFcZsZoneMemberIndex.description: An index value that uniquely identifies this Zone member among all Zone members in the Zone or Zone alias they belongs to.

h3cFcZsZoneMemberFormat.name: h3cFcZsZoneMemberFormat
h3cFcZsZoneMemberFormat.description: This object identifies the format of the Zone/Zone alias member's identifier that is contained in h3cFcZsZoneMemberIdentifier. This object cannot be modified while the value of the h3cFcZsZoneMemberRowStatus object is 'active'.

h3cFcZsZoneMemberIdentifier.name: h3cFcZsZoneMemberIdentifier
h3cFcZsZoneMemberIdentifier.description: This object contains the Member Identifier of the Zone or Zone alias. The interpretation of this object depends on the value of the corresponding instance of h3cFcZsZoneMemberFormat: - if h3cFcZsZoneMemberFormat is 'fcid', this object contains the 3-octet N_Port FC ID. - if h3cFcZsZoneMemberFormat is 'fwwn', this object contains an 8-octet F_Port WWN. - if h3cFcZsZoneMemberFormat is 'pwwn', this object contains an 8-octet N_Port WWN. - if h3cFcZsZoneMemberFormat is 'aliasName', this object contains the value of h3cFcZsZoneAliasName for some Zone alias in the same Zone Set Database. This object cannot be modified while the value of the h3cFcZsZoneMemberRowStatus object is 'active'.

h3cFcZsZoneMemberPairwiseRole.name: h3cFcZsZoneMemberPairwiseRole
h3cFcZsZoneMemberPairwiseRole.description: This object identifies the Pairwise role of the Zone/Zone alias member. If h3cFcZsZoneMemberFormat is 'aliasName', the value of this object can only be 'none'. If h3cFcZsZoneMemberFormat is not 'aliasName', the value of this object can't be 'none', and the default value is 'both' (including both 'initiator' and 'target' role). This object can be modified while the value of the h3cFcZsZoneMemberRowStatus object is 'active'. The Pairwise role of a port member takes effect only when the h3cFcZsZonePairwiseEnable of the Zone to which the port member belongs is set to 'true'.

h3cFcZsZoneMemberRowStatus.name: h3cFcZsZoneMemberRowStatus
h3cFcZsZoneMemberRowStatus.description: The status of this conceptual row.

h3cFcZsActivateTable.name: h3cFcZsActivateTable
h3cFcZsActivateTable.description: This table provides a mechanism to allow a Zone Set to be activated.

h3cFcZsActivateEntry.name: h3cFcZsActivateEntry
h3cFcZsActivateEntry.description: An entry contains information of the activation about a Zone Set.

h3cFcZsActivate.name: h3cFcZsActivate
h3cFcZsActivate.description: Name of the Zone Set that needs to be activated. The value of this object when read is always zero-length.

h3cFcZsDeactivate.name: h3cFcZsDeactivate
h3cFcZsDeactivate.description: A request to deactivate the currently active Zone Set. The value of this object when read is always 'noOper'. 'noOper' - Specifies no operation. 'deactivate' - Specifies the deactivate operation.

h3cFcZsActivateResult.name: h3cFcZsActivateResult
h3cFcZsActivateResult.description: As a result of the most recent activation/deactivation. 'none' - No activation/deactivation invoked since the last restart of the management system. 'inProcess' - Activation/deactivation is still in progress. 'activateSuccess' - Activation completed successfully. 'activateFailure' - Activation failed due to some reason. 'deactivateSuccess' - Deactivation completed successfully. 'deactivateFailure' - Deactivation failed due to some reason.

h3cFcZsActivateFailReason.name: h3cFcZsActivateFailReason
h3cFcZsActivateFailReason.description: The reason for the most recent failure of a Zone Set activation or deactivation. 'none' - No activation/deactivation invoked or the result of activation/deactivation is success. 'busy' - The management system is busy in some other process. 'activeZoneSetTooBig' - The Active Zone Set size in packet reached the maximum limit in Basic mode. 'noZoneSet' - No specified Zone Set found. 'noMember' - No port member found in the specified Zone Set.

h3cFcZsDistributeTable.name: h3cFcZsDistributeTable
h3cFcZsDistributeTable.description: This table provides an operational object to trigger a distribution for each existing VSAN.

h3cFcZsDistributeEntry.name: h3cFcZsDistributeEntry
h3cFcZsDistributeEntry.description: This entry provides an operational object to trigger a distribution for a specified VSAN.

h3cFcZsDistribute.name: h3cFcZsDistribute
h3cFcZsDistribute.description: Specifies the operation of triggering a distribution in this VSAN. 'noOper' - Specifies no operation. 'distribute' - Specifies the distribute operation.

h3cFcZsDistributeLastResult.name: h3cFcZsDistributeLastResult
h3cFcZsDistributeLastResult.description: Specifies the result of triggering a distribution for VSAN. 'none' - No distribution invoked via the corresponding instance of distribution. 'success' - Distribution completed successfully. 'inProgress' - Distribution is still in progress. 'rejectFailure' - Distribution failed due to an SW_RJT. 'otherFault' - Distribution/commit failed for some other reason.

h3cFcZsDistributeReasonCode.name: h3cFcZsDistributeReasonCode
h3cFcZsDistributeReasonCode.description: The reason code in the SW_RJT packet received in the most recent distribution. This object is meaningful only when the value of h3cFcZsDistributeLastResult is 'rejectFailure'.

h3cFcZsDistributeExplainCode.name: h3cFcZsDistributeExplainCode
h3cFcZsDistributeExplainCode.description: This object contains the corresponding reason code explanation for h3cFcZsDistributeReasonCode, and is meaningful only when the value of h3cFcZsDistributeLastResult is 'rejectFailure'.

h3cFcZsClearDatabaseTable.name: h3cFcZsClearDatabaseTable
h3cFcZsClearDatabaseTable.description: This table provides an operational object to clear the local Zone Set Database for each existing VSAN.

h3cFcZsClearDatabaseEntry.name: h3cFcZsClearDatabaseEntry
h3cFcZsClearDatabaseEntry.description: An entry provides an operational object to clear the local Zone Set Database for a specified VSAN.

h3cFcZsClearDatabase.name: h3cFcZsClearDatabase
h3cFcZsClearDatabase.description: Specify the operation of clearing local Zone Set Database in this VSAN. 'noOper' - Specifies no operation. 'clearDb' - Specifies clear operation.

h3cFcZsClearPktStatsTable.name: h3cFcZsClearPktStatsTable
h3cFcZsClearPktStatsTable.description: This table provides an operational object to clear the statistics on packets for each existing VSAN.

h3cFcZsClearPktStatsEntry.name: h3cFcZsClearPktStatsEntry
h3cFcZsClearPktStatsEntry.description: An entry provides an operational object to clear the statistics on packets for a specified VSAN.

h3cFcZsClearPktStats.name: h3cFcZsClearPktStats
h3cFcZsClearPktStats.description: Specify the operation of clearing the statistics on packets in this VSAN. 'noOper' - Specifies no operation. 'clearStats' - Specifies the clear operation.

h3cFcZsClearAllPktStats.name: h3cFcZsClearAllPktStats
h3cFcZsClearAllPktStats.description: An operational object to clear the statistics on packets for all existing VSANs. 'noOper' - Specifies no operation. 'clearStats' - Specifies the clear operation.

h3cFcZsActiveZoneTable.name: h3cFcZsActiveZoneTable
h3cFcZsActiveZoneTable.description: This table contains information about Active Zone in each existing VSAN.

h3cFcZsActiveZoneEntry.name: h3cFcZsActiveZoneEntry
h3cFcZsActiveZoneEntry.description: An entry contains information about Active Zone in a specified VSAN.

h3cFcZsActiveZonePairwiseEnable.name: h3cFcZsActiveZonePairwiseEnable
h3cFcZsActiveZonePairwiseEnable.description: Indicates whether Pairwise Zoning of an Active Zone is enabled.

h3cFcZsActiveMemberTable.name: h3cFcZsActiveMemberTable
h3cFcZsActiveMemberTable.description: This table contains information about Active Zone members in each existing VSAN.

h3cFcZsActiveMemberEntry.name: h3cFcZsActiveMemberEntry
h3cFcZsActiveMemberEntry.description: An entry contains information about Active Zone members in a specified VSAN.

h3cFcZsActiveMemberPairwiseRole.name: h3cFcZsActiveMemberPairwiseRole
h3cFcZsActiveMemberPairwiseRole.description: Indicates which role the Active Zone member is playing.

h3cFcZsServerStatusTable.name: h3cFcZsServerStatusTable
h3cFcZsServerStatusTable.description: This table contains the configuration and running state of each existing VSAN.

h3cFcZsServerStatusEntry.name: h3cFcZsServerStatusEntry
h3cFcZsServerStatusEntry.description: An entry contains the configuration and running state of a specified VSAN.

h3cFcZsServerStatus.name: h3cFcZsServerStatus
h3cFcZsServerStatus.description: The current status of Zone Server. 'free' - The Zone Server is now free. 'distribute' - The Zone Server is now busy distributing. 'merge' - The Zone Server is now busy merging.

h3cFcZsHardZoneStatus.name: h3cFcZsHardZoneStatus
h3cFcZsHardZoneStatus.description: The current status of Hard Zone Server. 'enable' - Hard Zone Server is enabled. 'adminDisable' - Hard Zone Server is disabled administratively. 'noResourceDisable' - Hard Zone Server is disabled due to lack of hardware resource.

h3cFcZsAliasCount.name: h3cFcZsAliasCount
h3cFcZsAliasCount.description: Number of Zone aliases that exist in the specified VSAN.

h3cFcZsZoneCount.name: h3cFcZsZoneCount
h3cFcZsZoneCount.description: Number of Zones that exist in the specified VSAN.

h3cFcZsZonesetCount.name: h3cFcZsZonesetCount
h3cFcZsZonesetCount.description: Number of Zone Sets that exist in the specified VSAN.

h3cFcZsPktStatsTable.name: h3cFcZsPktStatsTable
h3cFcZsPktStatsTable.description: Packet statistic table of Zone Servers.

h3cFcZsPktStatsEntry.name: h3cFcZsPktStatsEntry
h3cFcZsPktStatsEntry.description: An entry contains the statistics on packets of Zone Servers.

h3cFcZsPktInMergeReqCount.name: h3cFcZsPktInMergeReqCount
h3cFcZsPktInMergeReqCount.description: Number of Merge Request Frames received by local Zone Server from other Zone Servers.

h3cFcZsPktOutMergeReqCount.name: h3cFcZsPktOutMergeReqCount
h3cFcZsPktOutMergeReqCount.description: Number of Merge Request Frames sent by local Zone Server to other Zone Servers.

h3cFcZsPktInMergeAccCount.name: h3cFcZsPktInMergeAccCount
h3cFcZsPktInMergeAccCount.description: Number of Merge Accept Frames received by local Zone Server from other Zone Servers.

h3cFcZsPktOutMergeAccCount.name: h3cFcZsPktOutMergeAccCount
h3cFcZsPktOutMergeAccCount.description: Number of Merge Accept Frames sent by local Zone Server to other Zone Servers.

h3cFcZsPktInMergeRjtCount.name: h3cFcZsPktInMergeRjtCount
h3cFcZsPktInMergeRjtCount.description: Number of Merge Reject Frames received by local Zone Server from other Zone Servers.

h3cFcZsPktOutMergeRjtCount.name: h3cFcZsPktOutMergeRjtCount
h3cFcZsPktOutMergeRjtCount.description: Number of Merge Reject Frames sent by local Zone Server to other Zone Servers.

h3cFcZsPktInChangeReqCount.name: h3cFcZsPktInChangeReqCount
h3cFcZsPktInChangeReqCount.description: Number of change requests received by local Zone Server from other Zone Servers.

h3cFcZsPktOutChangeReqCount.name: h3cFcZsPktOutChangeReqCount
h3cFcZsPktOutChangeReqCount.description: Number of change requests sent by local Zone Server to other Zone Servers.

h3cFcZsPktInChangeAccCount.name: h3cFcZsPktInChangeAccCount
h3cFcZsPktInChangeAccCount.description: Number of Accept messages received from other Zone Servers in response to change request sent by local Zone Server.

h3cFcZsPktOutChangeAccCount.name: h3cFcZsPktOutChangeAccCount
h3cFcZsPktOutChangeAccCount.description: Number of Accept messages sent to other Zone Servers in response to change request received by local Zone Server.

h3cFcZsPktInChangeRjtCount.name: h3cFcZsPktInChangeRjtCount
h3cFcZsPktInChangeRjtCount.description: Number of Reject messages received from other Zone Servers in response to change request sent by local Zone Server.

h3cFcZsPktOutChangeRjtCount.name: h3cFcZsPktOutChangeRjtCount
h3cFcZsPktOutChangeRjtCount.description: Number of Reject messages sent to other Zone Servers in response to change request received by local Zone Server.

h3cFcZsZonesetNextFreeIndex.name: h3cFcZsZonesetNextFreeIndex
h3cFcZsZonesetNextFreeIndex.description: Specifies the latest available index of h3cFcZsZonesetIndex that can be used to identify a new Zone Set.

h3cFcZsZoneNextFreeIndex.name: h3cFcZsZoneNextFreeIndex
h3cFcZsZoneNextFreeIndex.description: Specifies the latest available index of h3cFcZsZoneIndex that can be used to identify a new Zone.

h3cFcZsZoneAliasNextFreeIndex.name: h3cFcZsZoneAliasNextFreeIndex
h3cFcZsZoneAliasNextFreeIndex.description: Specifies the latest available index of h3cFcZsZoneAliasIndex that can be used to identify a new Zone alias.

h3cFcZsZoneMemberNextFreeIndexTable.name: h3cFcZsZoneMemberNextFreeIndexTable
h3cFcZsZoneMemberNextFreeIndexTable.description: This table contains the information of the latest available index that can be used to identify a new member in each Zone or Zone alias.

h3cFcZsZoneMemberNextFreeIndexEntry.name: h3cFcZsZoneMemberNextFreeIndexEntry
h3cFcZsZoneMemberNextFreeIndexEntry.description: An entry contains the information of the latest available index that can be used to identify a new member in a Zone or Zone alias.

h3cFcZsZoneMemberNextFreeIndex.name: h3cFcZsZoneMemberNextFreeIndex
h3cFcZsZoneMemberNextFreeIndex.description: Specifies the latest available index of h3cFcZsZoneMemberIndex that can be used to identify a new member in a Zone or Zone alias.

h3cFcZsDefaultZoneChangedNotify.name: h3cFcZsDefaultZoneChangedNotify
h3cFcZsDefaultZoneChangedNotify.description: A h3cFcZsDefaultZoneChangedNotify notification is sent when the Default Zone setting of a specified VSAN is changed.

h3cFcZsHardZoneChangedNotify.name: h3cFcZsHardZoneChangedNotify
h3cFcZsHardZoneChangedNotify.description: A h3cFcZsHardZoneChangedNotify notification is sent when the hard Zone configuration of a specified VSAN is changed.

h3cFcZsMergeFailedNotify.name: h3cFcZsMergeFailedNotify
h3cFcZsMergeFailedNotify.description: A h3cFcZsMergeFailedNotify notification is sent when a Zone merge failure occurs.

h3cFcZsMergeSucceededNotify.name: h3cFcZsMergeSucceededNotify
h3cFcZsMergeSucceededNotify.description: A h3cFcZsMergeSucceededNotify notification is sent when a successful Zone merge occurs.

h3cFcZsActivationCompletedNotify.name: h3cFcZsActivationCompletedNotify
h3cFcZsActivationCompletedNotify.description: A h3cFcZsActivationCompletedNotify notification is sent whenever a activation/deactivation is completed.

h3cFcZsDefaultZoneChangedEnable.name: h3cFcZsDefaultZoneChangedEnable
h3cFcZsDefaultZoneChangedEnable.description: Indicates whether the module will generate traps for Default Zone setting change events.

h3cFcZsHardZoneChangedEnable.name: h3cFcZsHardZoneChangedEnable
h3cFcZsHardZoneChangedEnable.description: Indicates whether the module will generate traps for hard Zone change events.

h3cFcZsMergeFailedEnable.name: h3cFcZsMergeFailedEnable
h3cFcZsMergeFailedEnable.description: Indicates whether the module will generate traps for Zone merge failure events.

h3cFcZsMergeSucceededEnable.name: h3cFcZsMergeSucceededEnable
h3cFcZsMergeSucceededEnable.description: Indicates whether the module will generate traps for Zone merge success events.

h3cFcZsActivationCompletedEnable.name: h3cFcZsActivationCompletedEnable
h3cFcZsActivationCompletedEnable.description: Indicates whether the module will generate traps for activation/deactivation-completed events.

h3cFcZsLocalSwitchWWN.name: h3cFcZsLocalSwitchWWN
h3cFcZsLocalSwitchWWN.description: This object indicates the WWN of the local switch.

h3cFcZsPeerSwitchWWN.name: h3cFcZsPeerSwitchWWN
h3cFcZsPeerSwitchWWN.description: This object indicates the WWN of the peer switch.

h3cFcZsMergeFailCause.name: h3cFcZsMergeFailCause
h3cFcZsMergeFailCause.description: Indicates the reason of a Zone merge failure. 'zoneModeInconsistent' - The zone mode is inconsistent. 'zonePolicyNotEqual' - Zone Merge-Control setting or Default-Zone doesn't match. 'hardZoneInconsistent' - The Hard Zone Attribute is inconsistent. 'dataNotEqualInRestrict' - The Merge-Control setting is Restrict and the peer zoning database is not equal. 'activeZoneSetMergeFailed' - The Active Zone Set merge failed. 'zoneMergeDataTooBig' - The merged packet was too large. 'zoningObjectNumberTooBig' - The number of zoning objects exceeded the limit. 'zoneDbMergeFaildInBasic' - The database merge failed in Basic mode. 'zoneDbMergeFaildInEnhanced' - The database merge failed in Enhanced mode. 'other' - Unknown reason.
